trend_summary: Across the sequence the suburb grows gradually: new cul-de-sac housing fills forest gaps, small industrial sheds appear near the central highway, and a few northern fields rotate to mixed crops. No large high-rise clusters emerge; road grid and green buffers stay dominant, keeping a low-rise character while edge farmland persists.
notable_changes: Progressive infill of curvilinear housing tracts in the eastern‐central sector.
Expansion of light-industrial buildings beside the main north–south highway.
Clearing of scattered forest patches for new streets and lots.
Shift of some northern farmland blocks to different crop patterns.
Minor road widening and new roundabout at southern entrance.
